  "market_context": "Weekly chart showed a sweep of prior weekly high followed by bearish closure (CISD), establishing bearish bias. 4-hour structure revealed wick into opposing candle and FVG, with equal lows and SSL as targets. Analysis occurred during early trading session before NY open.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept the weekly swing high, closed back inside the range confirming bearish Change in State of Delivery (CISD), and formed a bearish continuation setup aligned across weekly, 4H, and 15M timeframes.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified on weekly chart that price swept a previous weekly high and closed back inside the range, confirming a bearish Change in State of Delivery (CISD).",
    "Step 2: Analyst noted failure swings on lower time frame and targeted a fair value gap (FVG) as the expected continuation zone for the weekly bearish move.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to 4-hour chart to assess structure, observing price forming a wick into an opposing candle and overlapping point of interest (FVG + high sweep), with closure back inside the prior bar.",
    "Step 4: Identified equal lows and previous low as sell-side liquidity (SSL) targets, and marked standard deviation projection levels for 3R reward.",
    "Step 5: On 15-minute chart, waited for and confirmed CISD via closure through up-close candles into the POI (FVG), then entered short at close with stop above the high, targeting SSL and standard deviation levels."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade executed short on 15-minute close after CISD; price continued lower through target, achieving ~3R profit.",
  "lessons": "Bearish continuation requires alignment: weekly CISD confirms bias, 4H wick/FVG provides structure, and 15M CISD at POI gives precise entry. Always confirm with multi-timeframe alignment before entering.",
